---
import Layout from '~/layouts/MarkdownLayout.astro';
const metadata = { title: 'Privacy Policy | Launch.Skin' };
---
<Layout frontmatter={metadata}>
<p><em>Last Updated: March 2026</em></p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>At Launch.Skin ("we," "our," or "us"), we specialize in providing professional identity solutions for elite skin practitioners. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, protect, and use the information necessary to launch and host your boutique clinical vanity URL and homepage.</p>

<h2>2. Information Collection</h2>
<p>To provide our white-glove setup service, we collect the following data points:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Clinic Identity:</strong> Business name, practitioner credentials, and professional bio.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Details:</strong> Professional email, phone number, and physical clinic address for your "Contact" section.</li>
    <li><strong>Digital Assets:</strong> High-resolution clinical imagery and logos provided by you for your homepage masterpiece.</li>
    <li><strong>Transactional Data:</strong> Payment information processed securely via third-party providers (PayPal). We do not store credit card numbers on our local servers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Usage of Information</h2>
<p>Your data is used exclusively to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provision and maintain your dedicated <strong>launch.skin</strong> vanity URL.</li>
    <li>Design and deploy your high-performance clinical homepage.</li>
    <li>Optimize your digital presence for local search authority and Google Maps signals.</li>
    <li>Communicate regarding technical updates or service enhancements.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Data Protection & Hosting</h2>
<p>We utilize enterprise-grade edge computing and SSL encryption to ensure your clinical storefront is secure from digital threats. Our "Zero-Maintenance" architecture means your data is not stored in a vulnerable database-driven CMS (like WordPress), significantly reducing the risk of data breaches.</p>

<h2>5. Third-Party Disclosure</h2>
<p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your clinical data. We only share information with essential infrastructure partners (e.g., domain registries and payment processors) required to keep your site live.</p>

<h2>6. Inquiries</h2>
<p>If you have questions about your data or wish to request a deletion of your digital address, please reach out to our team via our <a href="/contact">Support Page</a>.</p>
</Layout>
